caption:
The last time FC Barcelona won the Champions League was a decade ago — back in 2015. 🏆⬇️

What followed was a brutal stretch of heartbreaks and humiliations in Europe:

❌ 2016 – Knocked out by Atlético Madrid
❌ 2017 – Crushed by Juventus
❌ 2018 – Shocked by AS Roma after a 4–1 first-leg lead
❌ 2019 – Stunned by Liverpool’s iconic Anfield comeback
❌ 2020 – Destroyed 8–2 by Bayern Munich
❌ 2021 – Outclassed by PSG
❌ 2022 – Knocked out of the UCL group stage, then eliminated by Frankfurt in the Europa League
❌ 2023 – Another UCL group exit, followed by defeat to Manchester United in the UEL
❌ 2024 – Knocked out by PSG in the UCL once again

But now…
For the first time since 2019, FC Barcelona are back in the Champions League semifinals. 🥹👏

They finally look like the dominant force they once were in 2015 — hungry, focused, dangerous.
